<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FCA7FA35D88D39D3" box="[856,990,1507,1534]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. pindapoy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by BTA inserted dorsally on the tegulum, and from 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FC62F9D9DF5B3A0C" box="[925,1032,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. tutu¸A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF22CEF2FBE9F9D6DF3C3A0F" box="[1046,1135,1543,1569]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="175" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azaghal">azaghal</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF22CEF2FB7FF9D9DE5E3A0F" box="[1152,1293,1543,1570]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="175" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FB7FF9D9DE5E3A0F" box="[1152,1293,1543,1570]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF22CEF2FAE0F9D6DED33A0C" box="[1311,1408,1543,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="169.[136,235,1379,1403]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,198,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-264@169.[151,1436,189,1355]" captionTargetPageId="169" captionText="FIGURE 153. Actinopus itacolomi sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 18876: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597563/files/figure.png" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
A–C) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF22CEF2FC7DF9FDDF5E3A6B" box="[898,1037,1579,1606]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="175" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindapoy">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FC7DF9FDDF5E3A6B" box="[898,1037,1579,1606]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. pindapoy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by PS reaching less than the width of embolus. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF22CEF2FBBCF981DF803A47" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1091,1235,1616,1642]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="175" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FBBCF981DF803A47" box="[1091,1235,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share with 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF22CEF2FAA1F981DEFF3A47" box="[1374,1452,1616,1642]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="175" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tutu">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF22CEF2FAA1F981DEFF3A47" box="[1374,1452,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">A. tutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF22CEF2FCCDF9A2D8F83AA0" box="[818,939,1651,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 143" captionStartId="158.[136,235,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[189,1400,199,1627]" captionTargetId="figure-100@158.[151,1436,189,1643]" captionTargetPageId="158" captionText="FIGURE 143. Actinopus tutu sp. nov., male: A–C UFMG 585: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 5647: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597543/files/figure.png" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">Fig. 143 D</figureCitation>
) the similar subquadrate shape of receptacles. Males differ from those of the trilobate receptacles bearing a conspicouous lateral constriction.
</paragraph>
